	)
	(text "USB needs 90 Ohm differential traces. \nAccording to JLCPCB impedance calculator, with a JLC7628 prepreg and 6mil (0.15mm) space between lines\nI have to use 9 mil tracks -> 0.2mm. With a ground layer below\nFor USBC I will use a very short trace for D+ D- (around 2mm, very short, lower than critical length)\nThe Development board from ESP32 has no problem with these tracks despite being a 2 board layer and USB Data tracks too thin\nI have to place vias because of the pinout of USB C and CP2102. Some other people have placed vias without problems for signal integrity\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 39.37 133.985 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2 2)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "d9a22e0e-bf13-4790-bbd6-b33299d41a19")
	)
	(text "USB Hardware Design Guidelines for FTDI ICs p8 -> 10nF Cap + Ferrite Bead + 100nF Cap + 4.7uF Cap\nI disregarded such heavy filtering for the easier to implement 1uF and 100nF cap given in the CP2102 datasheet\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 38.735 106.045 0)
